---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import CallToAction from '../../components/CallToAction.astro';

import retailHero from '../../assets/retail-tobacco-field.jpg';
---

<Base
  title="Retail: Cigar & Tobacco"
  description="Mold ruins cigars and kills tobacco seedlings. ActivePure® reduces mold and fungi to safeguard humidors, lounges and indoor seed beds."
>
  <!-- The old page led with a placeholder heading ("IDENTIFY WHY RETAIL NEEDS OUR
       PRODUCT") followed by template filler about booking air travel. Both removed;
       the real subject of this page is cigar and tobacco mold. -->
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Retail: Cigar & Tobacco"
    title="Mold is the enemy of a good cigar"
    lead="Humidors need humidity — and humidity invites mold. The same technology that protects a hospital ward protects your inventory, your lounge and your customers."
    image={retailHero}
    imageAlt="Rows of tobacco plants in a field at harvest"
  />

  <Section>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-14">
      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-800 sm:text-3xl text-balance">
          What are the green-blue spots on my cigars?
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          <p>
            If you find blue or green spots on your cigars that leave a stain when you brush them off, the spots are
            probably mold. Mold is a damaging fungus that results from storing cigars in too high a humidity, and it
            will ruin the taste of your cigars.
          </p>
          <p>
            <em>Candida parapsilosis</em> and <em>Penicillium ascomycetous</em> are two common fungal names identified by
            a cigar mold study performed by an Australian biotech laboratory. Feeding on natural sugars secreted from the
            tobacco leaves, cigar mold can appear in many colors — white, red, green, blue or yellow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-800 sm:text-3xl text-balance">
          Tobacco indoor seed beds: mold &amp; fungi exposure
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          <p>
            Your indoor garden is never more vulnerable than in the first few weeks after you plant. Whether you start
            with seeds or clones, tender seedlings can suffer from overheating, underfeeding and lethal fungi.
          </p>
          <p>
            A very common problem when growing plants from seeds started indoors is the appearance of fuzzy white, gray
            or black mold that causes freshly sprouted seedlings to decay and collapse at the soil line. Collectively,
            the conditions caused by these fungi are known as "damping-off" disease — a death sentence for baby plants.
          </p>
          <p>
            Blue mold of tobacco, caused by <em>Peronospora hyoscyami</em> f.sp. <em>tabacina</em>, is a fungus-like
            organism that is highly destructive to tobacco seed beds, transplants and production fields in the humid
            farming zones of the southeastern and eastern United States, Canada, and countries bordering the Caribbean
            basin.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-accent-500 bg-brand-50 p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-800 sm:text-3xl">The answer</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
          <p>
            From the data of a study conducted at the Pittsburgh "Burn" Lounge between May 24th and June 6th, 2022,
            ActivePure® technology inactivated airborne <em>Aspergillus</em>/<em>Penicillium</em> mold
            <strong class="font-semibold text-brand-700"> to zero</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            ActivePure® technology greatly reduces mold and fungi levels to safeguard humidors and keep your product
            fresher for longer. From a manufacturing standpoint, we can safeguard your seedlings in the indoor grow
            space until they are ready to be transplanted into the field.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <figure class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 p-8">
        <blockquote class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
          <p>
            "The Tobacco Company utilizes Germ Solutions USA — ActivePure® technology to safeguard my staff and clients
            from COVID exposure, as well as our cigar investment within our humidors against the potential development
            of mold and fungus."
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-6 text-sm font-semibold text-brand-700">
          Greg Zimmerman <span class="font-normal text-slate-500">— President, PCA</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <CallToAction
    title="Protect your humidor and your lounge"
    lead="Tell us about your shop, lounge or seed beds and we will recommend the right configuration."
  />
</Base>
